title: 3rd Age Pickaxe
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: Requiring an attack level of 65 to wield and 61 Mining to use, the 3rd Age Pickaxe shares the same mining speed and special attack as the Dragon Pickaxe. The 3rd Age Pickaxe can be obtained as a possible reward from the master Treasure Trails.

title: Twisted Bow
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The twisted bow is a reward from the Chambers of Xeric that requires a Ranged level of 75 to wield. It can fire any type of arrow, including dragon arrows. The twisted bow is extremely valuable due to its unmatched power against monsters with a high magic level, such as Commander Zilyana. Similar to the crystal bow, the bow has an attack range of 10 tiles. As all attacks have a maximum of 10 range, long-range does not provide any attack distance benefit but may still be used to gain Defence XP. Read More.

title: 3rd Age Druidic Cloak
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: Requiring a prayer level of 65 to be worn, the 3rd Age Druid Cloak is part of the 3rd Age Druidic robes set, carrying the same stats as the Vestment Cloaks. The 3rd age Druid Cloak is a fabulously ancient vine cloak worn by the Druids of old.

title: Elysian Spirit Shield
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Elysian Spirit Shield is superior in both Melee and Ranged defense to that of the Arcane and Spectral Spirit Shield. The shield can be assembled by attaching an Elysian Sigil to a Blessed Spirit Shield. The Elysian Spirit Shield holds the position of highest crush defense in the shield slot and in terms of mitigating damage the shield is one of the most powerful in-game. To assemble the Elysian Spirit Shield players must possess level 90 Prayer and 85 Smithing. Read More.

title: Tumeken's Shadow
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: Tumeken's shadow is a two-handed powered staff requiring 85 Magic to wield, and is only available as a rare drop from the Tombs of Amascut. Powered by the sun itself, the staff was created by the god Tumeken during the Kharidian–Zarosian War as a means to fight back against the invading force of the Zarosian Empire. The staff has a built-in magic spell that can be used regardless of the player's current spellbook. The staff cannot be used to autocast any other combat spells.

title: 3rd Age Axe
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 30 minutes
description: Requiring an attack level of 65 to wield and Woodcutting 61 to use, the 3rd Age Axe shares the same cutting speed and special attack as a Dragon Axe. The 3rd Age Axe is a piece of the 3rd Age Equipment.The 3rd Age Axe is a beautifully crafted axe, shaped by ancient smiths.

title: Masori armour (f)
stockTooltip: In stock
description: Masori armour is a set of ranged armour requiring level 80 Ranged and 30 Defence to equip. The armour belonged to the Masori clan, who were powerful ranged weapon-wielders active around the time of the Kharidian–Zarosian War and were known for defending people from bandits who sought to take advantage of the wartime chaos.

title: Harmonised Orb
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Harmonised Orb is an item obtained as a drop from The Nightmare. It can be used on a nightmare staff to upgrade it to the harmonised nightmare staff. Once belonging to the shamans of Ashihama, the orb was used by the shamans to adapt the nightmare staff, its true name long since lost to the world, to any task, which gave them complete power over the island until the arrival of The Nightmare. Read More.

title: Torva platelegs
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Torva platelegs are part of the Torva armour set, requiring 80 Defence to wear. The platelegs boast the highest strength bonus of any legs slot equipment, being 2 higher than the Bandos tassets. As a Zarosian-aligned item, Torva armour will give Zarosian protection within the God Wars Dungeon.The platelegs are created by combining damaged Torva platelegs, obtained as a drop from Nex, with two Bandosian components. This process requires level 90 Smithing, and is not reversible.Read More.

title: Scythe of Vitur
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: Players can acquire the Scythe of Vitur in a rare drop from the Theatre of Blood. The Scythe is a two-handed slash weapon that requires 75 Attack and Strength to wield. The Scythe of Vitur can hit three enemies at once in a 1X3 arc in front of the player. The Scythe can be combined with the Holy Ornament Kit to make a Holy Scythe of Vitur. The Scythe of Vitur is a mighty scythe. Read More.

title: Christmas Cracker
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Christmas Cracker is a holiday item, originally dropped in the games first ever Christmas Event. Due to the climbing price of the Christmas Cracker, they are considered to be extremely rare; this is because of their ability to generate Partyhats. Additionally, it is because of their rarity that they are never sold on the Grand Exchange; instead, players choose to trade for coins/items because the value of Christmas Crackers exceeds the maximum of coins.Christmas Crackers are responsible for generating the first wearable discontinued rares. Read More.

title: Blue Partyhat
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: Blue Partyhats are some of the most expensive discontinued items within the game. Initially obtained in a 2001 Christmas event in which players opened Christmas Crackers to receive the item, the Blue Partyhat can no longer be acquired this way. If players wish to get their hands on this wearable item, they will need to trade with a player already possessing a Blue Partyhat. It is rumored the Blue Partyhat was originally stolen from Elfinlocks ashes by the Wise Old Man.  Read More.

title: White Partyhat
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: White Partyhats are a discontinued item that came from opening Christmas crackers, which were obtained in the 2001 Christmas event. They can no longer be obtained except for being traded from another player that already has one. Read More.

title: Red Partyhat
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Red Partyhat was originally obtained when players opened Christmas Crackers during a 2001 Christmas event; it has since become a discontinued item that can only be acquired through trades with other players. The Red Partyhat is one of the oldest discontinued items within the game, beaten only by the Pumpkin. When opening Christmas Crackers, players have a 32/128 chance of acquiring Red Partyhats. Read More.

title: Green Partyhat
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Green Partyhat is another discontinued item that was obtained through opening Christmas Crackers from the 2001 Christmas Event. Unfortunately, the Green Partyhat can only be obtained through trading with your fellow players since the discontinuation. As a result, this wearable item has become one of the most expensive items in the game's history.Green Partyhats are almost exclusively traded outside of the Grand Exchange due to their extreme value. Read More.

title: Purple Partyhat
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes

Since discontinuation, the Purple Partyhat can only be acquired through trades with other players. The Purple Partyhat is additionally used within the game as a symbol of wealth due to their high demand.Purple Partyhats are one of the most expensive items in the history of the game. Read More.

title: Yellow Partyhat
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes

title: Black Santa hat

description: The Black Santa Hat was released for players to obtain during the 15 Days of Christmas mini-event in 2013. The Black Santa Hat is now a tradable yet discontinued item. Players would acquire the Black Santa Hat by pulling on a Festive Cracker, and the Hat had a drop chance of 1 in 2000. The Black Santa Hat can be reversibly combined with a Santa Beard to obtain a Black Santa Hat with Beard. Read More.

title: Red santa Hat
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Red Santa Hat is a discontinued tradable item that made its appearance in RS on December 25th of, 2002, during a holiday event. Since then, Red Santa Hats have become a purely cosmetic item; this came following a game transition, meaning the Red Santa Hat has no equipment requirements, and stat bonuses were removed. The Red Santa Hat can be combined with a Santa Beard to create a Santa Hat with Beard. Read More.

title: Blue Hallowe'en Mask
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Blue Hallowe'en Mask was once the most expensive Hallowe'en Mask a player could get their hands on. However, the Blue Hallowe'en Mask now sits comfortably between its two counterparts on the expense scale. This Mask is a discontinued holiday item drop that took place on October 31st, 2002. The Blue Hallowe'en Mask can now no longer be obtained due to discontinuation, though those who were in possession of one will still own it. Read More.

title: Red Hallowe'en Mask
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes

However, there was a time that the Red Hallowe'en Masks' value surpassed that of the Red Partyhat. The Red Hallowe'en Mask is a tradable cosmetic item. Read More.

title: Green Hallowe'en Mask
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Green Hallowe'en Mask is a discontinued Holiday Drop item from an event that took place on October 31st, 2002. The Green Hallowe'en mask is one of three in its set, accompanied by the Red and Blue Hallowe'en Mask. Unfortunately, the Green Hallowe'en Mask experienced a price crash on December 25th, 2010, due to the announcement of the return of Free Trade. The Green Hallowe'en Mask will appear differently on the player wearing it, depending on them being male or female. Read More.

title: Disk of Returning
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Disk of Returning can be obtained by players when beginning a Midsummer Ritual during Midsummer Events. Players will need to be inside the Dwarven Mine to activate the Disk of Returning; doing so will transport them to the Blackhole. If a player attempts to activate the Disk of Returning in any other setting, they will be greeted with an error message. The Disk of Returning is used to get out of Thordur's Blackhole. Read More.

title: Pumpkin
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: The Pumpkin was the very first Holiday Item to be discontinued from the game. As Pumpkins were also the first Holiday Item to enter the game, they were not entirely understood; meaning players didn't feel the need to collect them. Pumpkins can be eaten in-game to heal a player by 200-900 life points, though due to their rarity, value, and status, Jagex issues a warning when a player tries to do so. Pumpkins were often used as currency to purchase the more expensive Partyhat. Read More.

title: Easter Egg
stockTooltip: Expect delivery of this product within 10 minutes
description: Easter Eggs were originally obtained in an Easter Event drop taking place on March 31st, 2002. The Easter Egg is an edible item, and when a player does so, they are healed between 200-900 Life Points. Commonly thought of as useless, many players ate or discarded their eggs, leading to a warning message appearing when a player attempts to do so. The Easter Egg is not to be mistaken with the Chocolate Eggs given as rewards in the 2008 Easter event.  Read More.
